A fair six-sided die is rolled twice. The first roll determines the row of a 3x3 grid, and the second roll determines the column. If the grid has the following pattern of shaded squares, what is the probability that the die lands on a shaded square?

[asy]
unitsize(1cm);
fill((0,0)--(1,0)--(1,1)--(0,1)--cycle,gray(0.7));
fill((1,1)--(2,1)--(2,2)--(1,2)--cycle,gray(0.7));
fill((2,0)--(3,0)--(3,1)--(2,1)--cycle,gray(0.7));
draw((0,0)--(3,0)--(3,3)--(0,3)--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw((0,1)--(3,1),linewidth(0.7));
draw((0,2)--(3,2),linewidth(0.7));
draw((1,0)--(1,3),linewidth(0.7));
draw((2,0)--(2,3),linewidth(0.7));
[/asy]

