Set $S$ is a set of triangles such that (1) only the grid points shown here are used as vertices, (2) all sides are vertical or horizontal and (3) no two triangles in the set are congruent. If $S$ contains the maximum possible number of triangles given these conditions, what fraction of the triangles in set $S$ are isosceles? Express your answer as a common fraction. [asy]import graph;
size(50);
for(int i = 0; i<5; ++i)
for(int j = 0; j<5; ++j)
fill(Circle((i,j),.1));
[/asy]

