A hiker starts at point $B$ in the diagram below and randomly selects one of the three possible directions with equal probability. Each time she comes to an intersection, she again randomly selects one of the possible directions. What is the probability that, in her first three steps, she will walk completely around the blue triangle? Express your answer as a common fraction. [asy]size(100);
fill((1,1)--(1,2)--(2,1)--cycle, blue(.6));
draw((0,0)--(0,3)--(3,3)--(3,0)--cycle, linewidth(1.5));
draw((0,1)--(3,1), linewidth(1.5));
draw((0,2)--(3,2), linewidth(1.5));
draw((1,0)--(1,3), linewidth(1.5));
draw((2,0)--(2,3), linewidth(1.5));
dot(MP("B", (2,2), NW));
[/asy]

