For $x \ge 1,$ let $h$ be the function defined as follows:
\[h(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor x \rfloor \left| x - \lfloor x \rfloor - \dfrac{1}{3 \lfloor x \rfloor} \right| & \text{if $x < \lfloor x \rfloor + \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor}$}, \\
h \left( x - \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor} \right) & \text{otherwise}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Let $j(x) = 3^{x - 2010}.$ Compute the number of points in which the graphs of $h$ and $j$ intersect.

For $x \ge 1,$ let $k$ be the function defined as follows:
\[k(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor x \rfloor \left| x - \lfloor x \rfloor - \dfrac{1}{4 \lfloor x \rfloor} \right| & \text{if $x < \lfloor x \rfloor + \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor}$}, \\
k \left( x - \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor} \right) & \text{otherwise}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Let $l(x) = 4^{x - 2013}.$ Compute the number of points in which the graphs of $k$ and $l$ intersect.

For $x \ge 1,$ let $m$ be the function defined as follows:
\[m(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor x \rfloor \left| x - \lfloor x \rfloor - \dfrac{1}{5 \lfloor x \rfloor} \right| & \text{if $x < \lfloor x \rfloor + \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor}$}, \\
m \left( x - \dfrac{1}{\lfloor x \rfloor} \right) & \text{otherwise}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Let $n(x) = 5^{x - 2016}.$ Compute the number of points in which the graphs of $m$ and $n$ intersect.

